edu.first.identifiers

Interface Switch


  • public interface Switch
    A switch is a manipulatable state with 2 possible values: on and off. A position can be virtually anything that can be set to a boolean in some sense, but should make sense in the context of a "position". It should be capable of being in either position at any time.
    Since:
    May 22 13

    • Method Detail

      • setPosition

        void setPosition(boolean pos)
        Changes the position to the designated value. In general, there should be no delay between the time this method is called, and when the value is actually set.
        Parameters:
        pos - new position to set the switch to
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when value cannot be set
